nd indicates the number of clicks remaining. I'll refine the `index.html` colors to create the darker themed look, and the button will be yellow/orange. Now I am trying to figure out which URL to use in the `window.open`.\n\n\n**Refining Ad Trigger Logic**\n\nI'm now focusing on ensuring the new window behavior. To trigger the browser's popup mechanism, I'll use `window.open(location.href, '_blank', 'width=100,height=100,left=10000,top=10000')` to encourage the desired behavior. My plan is to update `index.html` with deeper colors and adjust the React logic, including button text, and verifying that the `REQUIRED_CLICKS` are 2. I'll test how the `window.open` call works for the first two clicks. The \"new window\" means that the second click, should open a new window instead of a new tab. I'm experimenting with direct links and the Monetag script behavior within `window.open`.\n\n\n**Refining Ad Trigger Sequence**\n\nNow, I'm focusing on the click sequence: the first two clicks trigger new ad windows, and the third click navigates to Google Drive. The `window.open` calls will be crucial to ensure the ads open in new windows, not just tabs. I'll meticulously update the React logic to handle these three states. Finally, I'm adjusting the color scheme to meet the user's requirements - I will now use a darker palette of black, purple, green, and orange/yellow. I am going to modify the `index.html` to reflect the changes.\n\n\n",
